data.name: Hydrite Chemical Co.
data.description:
Hydrite, a family-owned company established in 1929, is one of the largest independent providers of chemicals and related services in the United States. Headquartered in Brookfield, Wisconsin, Hydrite has a network of manufacturing facilities, warehouses, and laboratories in Wisconsin, Illinois, Iowa, Indiana, California, Colorado, and Texas with over 1,000 employees throughout the United States.  Hydrite owns and operates a private fleet including tractors, van trailers, tankers, and railcars.


Hydrite focuses on chemical distribution and manufacturing, food and dairy sanitation, organic processing, liquid sulfites, foam control, and water treatment chemistries


With a diverse product portfolio, Hydrite’s dedicated chemists, engineers, and technical service staff have extensive knowledge and experience in solving the most challenging formulating

problems.  Hydrite is strongly committed to quality and customer responsiveness and offers superior products and innovative solutions.

data.name: Suppressor
data.description: Suppressor is an effective solution for managing foam-related issues in various industries. Acting as an anti-foaming agent, defoamer, and deaerator, it ensures smooth operations without compromising quality. Its key features include being formaldehyde-free, low-toxicity, non-hazardous, organic, and silicone-free, making it environmentally friendly and safe to use. Compatible with a range of polymers and resins, including acrylics, epoxies (EP), latex, and styrene acrylics, it offers versatility in applications. Utilizing a radiation cure method, it is suitable for adhesive and sealant types like glue, providing reliable performance in diverse settings.

data.name: Suppressor 2333
data.description: Suppressor 2333 is formulated from a series of synthetic bases that affords the end-user a very efficient defoamer/antifoam with little to no effects that are prevalent with many of the commercially available defoamers. The product is very efficient in releasing entrained air in high viscosity media such as inks/coating, adhesives, and resins/polymers.

data.name: Suppressor ORG 60
data.description: Suppressor ORG 60 is a foam control chemistry in a new line of organic products from Hydrite Chemical Co. that affords the end-user a powerful foam control agent for systems that require the highest level of approval for organic processing. The product can be used to treat foam in systems such as vegetable washing, meat processing, dairy processing and fertilizers where organic approvals are strictly required.

data.name: Suppressor 3471
data.description: Suppressor 3471 is a product that affords the end-user a very efficient foam control agent for systems high in starch and protein. The product can be used to treat foam found in cheese, whey and lactose manufacturing processes. In food applications, Suppressor 3471 should be metered into the system as received.

data.name: Suppressor 3548
data.description: Suppressor 3548 is based upon a synthetic base that affords the specialty processor the ability to use in a variety of systems. The product is designed for harsh environments such as high alkalinity, high salinity, and low pH systems. In most processing, Suppressor 3548 should be used as received.

data.name: Suppressor 2222
data.description: Suppressor 2222 is a 100% active hyper branched polymer defoamer. Unlike conventional defoamers, Suppressor 2222 has performance benefits on the molecular level. Its high efficiency can allow for 25-50% less dosage while maintaining excellent persistence in most systems. This product also utilizes unique wetting properties.

data.name: Suppressor 2233
data.description: Suppressor 2233 is a mineral oil-based foam control agent designed to deliver effective control of foam. The product will work very well in most paint and coating systems. The product works particularly well in systems where resin content is based upon acrylics. Suppressor 2233 also works well as a grind defoamer.

data.name: Suppressor 2238
data.description: Suppressor 2238 is a mineral oil-based foam control agent enhanced with surfactants to deliver effective control of foam. The product will work very well in most paint and coating systems. The product works particularly well in systems where resin content is based upon acrylics. Suppressor 2238 also works very well as a grind defoamer.

data.name: Suppressor 1615
data.description: Suppressor 1615 is a hybrid defoamer combining silicone and fatty alcohol technologies to create a synergistic foam control product. The product works better than many silicones and will compete with most fatty alcohols. Suppressor 1615 is a great product to use where environmental impact is a main concern.

data.name: Suppressor 3721
data.description: Suppressor 3721 is based upon a 100% active synthetic base that affords the operator the freedom to use the product to control foam in many food processing systems as well as many industrial applications. The specific molecular weight of the molecule provides efficient control of foam throughout fermentation applications.

data.name: Suppressor 3415
data.description: Suppressor 3415 is a proprietary blend designed for use in potato processing areas. This product is an optimized blend of materials. Improved knockdown and persistence are fundamental additions for this defoamer. This product works effectively in push water systems where the defoamer is diluted with water before it is transported to the application point.

data.name: Suppressor 3610
data.description: Suppressor 3610 is a food-grade foam control agent designed to control foam in food-processing plants. The product controls foam efficiently and offers the operator a product that is relatively easy to use. It can also be used in potato processing systems.

data.name: Suppressor 3583
data.description: Suppressor 3583 is a new technology that affords the end-user a very efficient foam control agent for systems high in starch content such as potato processing. The product can also be used to treat foam found in vegetable washing operations, or cheese manufacturing. This product does not contain any free silicone.

data.name: Suppressor 3210
data.description: Suppressor 3210 is a Kosher approved, 10% active silicone emulsion designed for use in food- processing areas where additives are required to conform to direct food contact regulations. The product offers the customer effective foam control at a relatively low cost. Quick knockdown of foam and persistent foam control marks the characteristics of Suppressor 3210 in most systems. The product works equally well in hot and cold systems.

data.name: Suppressor 3512
data.description: Suppressor 3512 is a 100% active product that operates effectively in a variety of applications. It was specifically designed to deliver high performance in the fermentation processing industry. This silicone-free defoamer allows for a low toxicity profile and is dispersible in water-based systems. In addition, this product will not impact oxygen transfer pathways that can influence growth rates in a fermentation stream.

data.name: Suppressor 3522
data.description: Suppressor 3522 is a formulated product designed specifically for sugar processing. The product works very well in controlling foam in many of the processing areas. Specifically, Suppressor 3522 was designed for maximum efficiency in the flume area of the sugar processing mill.

data.name: Suppressor 3540
data.description: Suppressor 3540 is based upon a synthetic base that affords the specialty formulator the ability to prepare defoamers/antifoams. This product can be used to control foam in many processing systems. The product is recommended to be used at use levels between 10-100 ppm in most applications.

data.name: Suppressor 3548
data.description: Suppressor 3548 is based upon a synthetic base that affords the specialty processor the ability to use in a variety of systems. The product is designed for harsh environments such as high alkalinity, high salinity, and low pH systems. In most processing, Suppressor 3548 should be used as received.

data.name: Suppressor 3533
data.description: Suppressor 3533 is formulated product designed specifically for sugar processing. The product works very well in controlling foam in many areas within the sugar processing mills. The specific construction of the molecule provides efficient control of foam throughout most sugar applications.

data.name: Suppressor 3519
data.description: Suppressor 3519 is an effective antifoam designed to eliminate foam that develops in many processes. The product is very well adapted to work in fermentation media that contain varying levels of solids. The main reasons for using Suppressor 3519 in fermentation media are that it has extremely low toxicity to microbial organisms, silicone free, and will not affect oxygen transfer pathways. The product also is not affected by sterilization and works over a broad temperature range.

data.name: Suppressor 3130
data.description: Suppressor 3130 is a Kosher approved, 30% active silicone emulsion designed for use in food- processing areas where additives are required to conform to direct food contact regulations. The product offers the customer effective foam control at a relatively low cost. Quick knockdown of foam and persistent foam control marks the characteristics of Suppressor 3130 in most systems. The product works equally well in hot and cold systems. Suppressor 3130 can also be diluted to prepare 10% silicone antifoams.

data.name: Suppressor 3592
data.description: Suppressor 3592 is based on a synthetic base that affords the operator the freedom to use in many systems. The product can be used to control foam in many processing systems and works especially well in hot systems. The specific molecular weight of the molecule provides efficient control of foam throughout most applications. The product works well in boiler applications.

data.name: Suppressor 3471
data.description: Suppressor 3471 is a product that affords the end-user a very efficient foam control agent for systems high in starch and protein. The product can be used to treat foam found in cheese, whey and lactose manufacturing processes. In food applications, Suppressor 3471 should be metered into the system as received.

data.name: Suppressor 3721
data.description: Suppressor 3721 is based upon a 100% active synthetic base that affords the operator the freedom to use the product to control foam in many food processing systems as well as many industrial applications. The specific molecular weight of the molecule provides efficient control of foam throughout fermentation applications.

data.name: Suppressor 3569
data.description: Suppressor 3569 is one in a series of new synthetic technology that affords the end-user a very efficient foam control agent for systems high in starch content such as potato processing. The product can also be used to treat foam found in vegetable washing operations.

data.name: Suppressor 3590
data.description: Suppressor 3590 is a new synthetic technology that affords the end-user a very efficient control agent for systems high in starch content such as potato processing. This product is recommended to be used at use levels between 10-100 ppm in most applications.

data.name: Suppressor 2238
data.description: Suppressor 2238 is a mineral oil-based foam control agent enhanced with surfactants to deliver effective control of foam. The product will work very well in most paint and coating systems. The product works particularly well in systems where resin content is based upon acrylics. Suppressor 2238 also works very well as a grind defoamer.

data.name: Suppressor 2225
data.description: Suppressor 2225 is a mineral oil based foam control agent designed to deliver effective control of foam problems at an efficient level. The product works well in many systems, and can be diluted in mineral oil to form stable suspension for re-sale. Suppressor 2225 also works well as an antifoam for soluble oils in the metal working industry and as a base for pulp mill defoamer formulations.

data.name: Suppressor 1310
data.description: Suppressor 1310 is a 10% active silicone emulsion designed for general purpose use in controlling foam. The product offers the customer effective foam control at a relatively low cost. Quick knockdown of foam and persistent foam control marks the characteristics of Suppressor 1310 in most systems. The product works equally well in hot and cold systems.

data.name: Suppressor 1100
data.description: Suppressor 1100 is a high-solids emulsion of wax and proprietary blends that affords the end-user versatile foam control in a stable package. The product works exceptionally well in those systems that encounter foam derived from microbial metabolism resulting in persistent, brown-gray foam. Suppressor 1100 works very well in eliminating entrained air in systems where it is a problem.

data.name: Suppressor 2231
data.description: Suppressor 2231 is a mineral oil-based foam control agent designed to deliver effective control of foam problems at an efficient level. The product works well in most aqueous systems. The product works particularly well in systems where polymer content is based upon styrenated acrylics and/or latex. Extreme pH and/or salinity have relatively little effect on efficiency.

data.name: Suppressor 1194
data.description: Suppressor 1194 is an emulsion foam control agent designed to deliver effective control of foam. The product will work very well in most paint and coating systems. The product works particularly well in systems where resin content is based upon acrylics.

data.name: Suppressor 2360
data.description: Suppressor 2360 is a 100% active defoamer/antifoam. The product is designed to use in those applications where foam is generated by microbes and BOD dissolved in the effluent. Suppressor 2360 exhibits quick flash knockdown and excellent overall persistence when used to deal with biological foam applications in wastewater treatment.

data.name: Suppressor 3120
data.description: Suppressor 3120 is a Kosher approved, 20% active silicone emulsion designed for use in food- processing areas where additives are required to conform to direct food contact regulations. The product offers the customer effective foam control at a relatively low cost. Quick knockdown of foam and persistent foam control marks the characteristics of Suppressor 3120 in most systems. The product works equally well in hot and cold systems. Suppressor 3120 can also be diluted to prepare 10% silicone antifoams.

data.name: Suppressor 1135
data.description: Suppressor 1135 is a high-solids emulsion of wax and proprietary blends that affords the end-user a versatile foam control agent. The product works well in high surfactant loadings as well as those systems that encounter foam derived from microbial metabolism resulting in persistent, brown-gray foam. Suppressor 1135 should be evaluated in systems where air entrainment is a severe problem.

data.name: Suppressor 1120
data.description: Suppressor 1120 is a relatively high-solids emulsion of wax and proprietary blends that affords the end-user a versatile foam control agent. The product works well in high surfactant loadings as well as those systems that encounter foam derived from microbial metabolism resulting in persistent, brown-gray foam.

data.name: Suppressor 2353
data.description: Suppressor 2353 is 100% active defoamer/antifoam. The product is designed to use in those applications where foam is generated by microbes and BOD dissolved in the effluent. Suppressor 2353 exhibits excellent overall persistence when used to deal with biological foam applications in wastewater treatment.

data.name: Suppressor 1723
data.description: Suppressor 1723 is a 45% active organic silicone emulsion designed for high-end use applications where compatibility is a must. The characteristics of this product in most dye systems include: quick knockdown of foam, persistent foam control, and release of entrained air. This product works equally well in hot and cold systems. Suppressor 1723 can also be diluted to prepare 10% silicone antifoams.

data.name: Suppressor 1128
data.description: Suppressor 1128 is formulated as a highly active foam control product for water and wastewater treatment systems. The product is an emulsion of fatty alcohols and specialty surfactants that affords the end-user efficient foam control at a relatively low overall operating cost.

data.name: Suppressor 2237
data.description: Suppressor 2237 is a mineral oil-based foam control agent designed to deliver effective control of foam problems at an efficient level. The product works very well as a general purpose foam control agent in construction, coatings, adhesives, and a variety of other media. Suppressor 2237 was designed to be a package stable defoamer/antifoam.

data.name: Suppressor 2132
data.description: Suppressor 2132 is a low molecular weight compound that is useful in difficult systems where persistent foam cannot be resolved with ordinary foam control agents. The product is especially useful for controlling foam in UV-EB curable systems where quick dissipation of entrained air is required to produce the desired product. Suppressor 2132 eliminates unwanted air entrainment, as well as micro- and macro- foam, without adverse effects such as pinholes and craters.

data.name: Suppressor 2369
data.description: Suppressor 2369 is 100% active defoamer/antifoam. The product is designed to use in the most difficult foaming systems when nothing else works. Suppressor 2369 works great where the presence of Nocardia and Microthrix exacerbate the foam and treatment thereof. In most foaming applications, Suppressor 2369 should be metered into the system as received for optimal performance.

data.name: Suppressor 2222
data.description: Suppressor 2222 is a 100% active hyper branched polymer defoamer. Unlike conventional defoamers, Suppressor 2222 has performance benefits on the molecular level. Its high efficiency can allow for 25-50% less dosage while maintaining excellent persistence in most systems. This product also utilizes unique wetting properties.

data.name: Suppressor 1155
data.description: Suppressor 1155 is a low solids wax emulsion that affords the end-user efficient foam control at a relatively low overall cost. The product works well in wastewater systems where low BOD-COD levels are desired and for foam control in cooling towers. Suppressor 1155 offers efficient control where no oil sheen, as well as little environmental impact, is required.

data.name: Suppressor 3105
data.description: Suppressor 3105 is a Kosher approved 5% active silicone emulsion designed for use in food- processing areas where additives are required to conform to direct food contact regulations. The product offers the customer effective foam control at a relatively low cost. Quick knockdown of foam and persistent foam control marks the characteristics of Suppressor 3105 in most systems. The product works equally well in hot and cold systems.

data.description: Suppressor 2233 is a mineral oil-based foam control agent designed to deliver effective control of foam. The product will work very well in most paint and coating systems. The product works particularly well in systems where resin content is based upon acrylics. Suppressor 2233 also works well as a grind defoamer.
